Raymond et al. (2003) noticed that all three events displayed transient brightennings in the [Fe XVIII] line and little or none of the cool gas that usually dominates UVCS spectra of CMEs, and that the violent disruption of the pre-CME streamer was manifested by splitting of the low temperature (2.9×105K\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
