Following McKenzie and Hudson (1999) and McKenzie (2000), Sheeley and Wang (2002) identified downward motions of the coronal mass at the heliocentrical distance from 2 to 6 R⊙, with each flow at speed varying from 50 to 100kms−1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
